The Midway Continued
Bozo
The first thing I went on in the Midway was Bozo. It was awfully thrilling.  When you got inside you ride around a little bit with the curtains up, then they go down and everything is pitch black. It is something like a roller coaster but it is not as high or as big, but it goes around more times.
The Rapids
The Rapids is a big barrel that you get in and away you go over the Rapids. Every time we went over a bump, I nearly fell off my seat. It was real dark all the time and it went faster then [sic] Bozo did, it took my breath away.

Claire Lieber Crews Century of Progress Notebook

The Midget Village
In the Midget Village they have very small midgets. 
They have midgets who sell candy, cut hair, they have a zoo and a show. The show was awfully nice they had a band, tap dancing, singing and a man who did tricks with a piece of rope. They also have a restaurant.
Ripleys Believe It Or Not
In Ripleys we saw a man forty five years old turning to stone. A baby with perfectly normal parents with three arms and four legs. A half girl that was fourteen years old. A man that could balance ten billiard balls in each hand, and later nine legal baseballs in each hand. A man that could swallow a light, a watch, and some money and make them all come up again one at a time. A man with a Lepoardskin [sic]. A man with Elephant skin. A lady with skin that when she

ObjectName: Claire Lieber Crews Century of Progress Notebook
Claire Lieber Crews Century of Progress Notebook
Claire Lieber Crews Century of Progress Notebook

element_texts.text: Completed

pulled it snapped right back into place so she is called the lady with rubber skin. There was a chair made out of corks. The word count written 1000 times on a grain of rice and a great many other interesting things.
While we were watching one of the performances the usher said, "Where Rog and Billy," they came to the ushers and he said, "Your mother and father are waiting outside with some Ice cream cones for you."
Afterwards he told us they had been in Ripleys for four hours. 
The Mirror House
I went in the Mirror House alone and was it fun. 
There was a boy there that came up to me and said "Are you the genuine"? There are nothing but mirrors

Once when I was trying to get out in a hurry to see "Wings of a Century" I bumped smack into a mirror but I kept wandering around. I thought I wouldn't ever get out but I finally did.
An Airplane Ride
One Sunday when I was down at the Fair I went for a ride on an airplane in the Midway.
We went up, up, up, in the airplane finally we got so high and it got real breezy that my good Sunday hat blew off. We found it later. 
We could make the airplane dive, tip its wings, or go very high.
The Pantheon
The Pantheon has in it a great circlerama which has pictures of the countries in the war  Some of the pictures of

ObjectName: Claire Lieber Crews Century of Progress Notebook

the countries are, France, Belgium, Germany, Serbia, Great Britain, United States, and many others.
It is 120 ft long and 60 ft high. Two great men painted it besides 118 other artists. It came from France for a Century of Progress and took many years to paint.
The Battle of Gettysburg
The Battle of Gettysburg is something like the Pantheon but it does not tell about the circlerama itself but the Battle of Gettysburg. It shows marvelous illumination of how the soldiers were and what they were doing at morning, day-time, and a [sic] night, also the sunset was beautiful.

Laff in the Dark
Laff in the Dark is a very thrilling ride in which whenever you least suspect it a goblin skelton or ghost jump's at you. It is dark and spooky and three people ride at once in a little car -like.
The Monsters
The Monsters is a place where they have big poisonous snakes and Chinese Dragons. There is a man there that lets himself get bitten by poisonous snakes he does not die and he is always in with the snakes. 
He said to a woman "For a dime I will tell you your first name." The woman gave him a dime because she didn't think

that he could guess her first name and he said that if he didn't guess it right he would give her back her dime.
He said raise your right hand and swear that you'll tell the truth about it, the woman did, and he said "your first name was baby."
Africa
Africa is a big place where the natives of Africa are. There are Pigmies and other savages. They do many ceremonial dances. There was an African Prince there who could talk our language.
It was very interesting to see the savages ways.

The Ferris Wheel

It goes around in a circle about ten times and goes over lots of bumps and in and out. I had a grand time on it.

The Fair
The Fair is on the lake front from 18th street to 31st street. It can be reached by train, bus, car, or street-car. It took three years to build it.
The Fair is gorgeous, splendifferous, but garish. The buildings are beautiful as well as the Fair.
At nighttime around 8.30 P.M. they light up the Fair by sending a ray from the Hall of Science to every point. Everything is beautifully lighted.
The colors are magnificent and very bright. It is like Fairy-land come true.
The sight of the lagoon in the center is very pretty for the eyes to see the motor boats, speed boats, and Gondolas to ride in.
They used to have a little bit of an Island for the planetarium but now they have a great big one for the Fair. It is called the Northerly Island.

ObjectName: Claire Lieber Crews Century of Progress Notebook
Claire Lieber Crews Century of Progress Notebook

The Fair Continued
Just some of the Fair is on the Island. The Island the Planetarium is on was made bigger so part of the Fair could be built there too.
Besides the exhibits, buildings, the Enchanted Island, and other things they have a barge that has a free show in it.
When the Fair opened they had fireworks every night which were beautiful.
I like the Fair so much that I can't wait to see all of it.
The buildings in the Fair are not like the buildings in the old Fair but are more cheaply made
The Fair is going to be carried over to 1934 because it was such a success in 1933.
